			<div class="col-md-11 col-sm-11 col-xs-12 no-padding">
				<h1>Vulnerable WordPress Leads to Security Blog Infection</h1>
<div class="excerpt">Even visiting security-oriented websites can sometimes be&nbsp;risky. If you&rsquo;ve visited the security blog zerosecurity.org this month and you&rsquo;re also a user of ESET&rsquo;s security products, you might have encountered an anti-virus alert such as this one: The detection names may vary. Different variants of the following &ldquo;generic families&rdquo; were detected on the compromised websites on</div>
<div class="post-meta">
    <div class="wls-authors">
            </div>
    <span class="meta">
		<span class="strong">
			<time datetime="2012-03-27 08:38:29">27 Mar 2012 - 08:38AM</time>
